    "id": "s2",
    "title": "Numbers and Basic Questions",
    "description": "Master counting and asking simple questions like \"How many?\".",
    "level": "Beginner",
    "content": "<p>Numbers are fundamental for daily interactions. Let's learn to count:</p><h3>Numbers 1-10:</h3><ol><li><strong>Uno</strong></li><li><strong>Dos</strong></li><li><strong>Tres</strong></li><li><strong>Cuatro</strong></li><li><strong>Cinco</strong></li><li><strong>Seis</strong></li><li><strong>Siete</strong></li><li><strong>Ocho</strong></li><li><strong>Nueve</strong></li><li><strong>Diez</strong></li></ol><h3>Numbers 11-20:</h3><ol start=\"11\"><li><strong>Once</strong></li><li><strong>Doce</strong></li><li><strong>Trece</strong></li><li><strong>Catorce</strong></li><li><strong>Quince</strong></li><li><strong>Dieciséis</strong> (10 + 6)</li><li><strong>Diecisiete</strong> (10 + 7)</li><li><strong>Dieciocho</strong> (10 + 8)</li><li><strong>Diecinueve</strong> (10 + 9)</li><li><strong>Veinte</strong></li></ol><h3>Tens and Beyond:</h3><ul><li><strong>Veinte:</strong> 20</li><li><strong>Treinta:</strong> 30</li><li><strong>Cuarenta:</strong> 40</li><li><strong>Cincuenta:</strong> 50</li><li><strong>Sesenta:</strong> 60</li><li><strong>Setenta:</strong> 70</li><li><strong>Ochenta:</strong> 80</li><li><strong>Noventa:</strong> 90</li><li><strong>Cien:</strong> 100</li><li><strong>Mil:</strong> 1,000</li><li><strong>Un millón:</strong> 1,000,000</li></ul><h3>Numeration:</h3><p>To form numbers between 21 and 29, you can simply combine <em>veinti-</em> with the digit, for example, <strong>veintiuno</strong> (21) and <strong>veinticinco</strong> (25).</p><p>For numbers 31 and above, you use the ten's place followed by \"y\" (and) and the digit. For example:</p><ul><li><strong>Treinta y uno:</strong> 31</li><li><strong>Cuarenta y dos:</strong> 42</li><li><strong>Ochenta y nueve:</strong> 89</li></ul><h3>Basic Questions:</h3><p>To ask \"How many?\":</p><p class=\"example-text\"><strong>¿Cuántos/Cuántas?</strong> (Use <em>cuántos</em> for masculine nouns, <em>cuántas</em> for feminine nouns)</p><p>Examples:</p><p class=\"example-text\"><strong>¿Cuántos libros tienes?</strong> (How many books do you have?)</p><p class=\"example-text\"><strong>¿Cuántas manzanas quieres?</strong> (How many apples do you want?)</p><p>Other useful questions:</p><ul><li><strong>¿Qué?</strong> (What?)</li><li><strong>¿Quién?</strong> (Who?)</li><li><strong>¿Dónde?</strong> (Where?)</li></ul>"
