    "level": "Beginner",
    "content": "<p>Spanish nouns have gender (masculine or feminine) and number (singular or plural). Articles must agree with the noun.</p><h3>Definite Articles (The):</h3><ul><li><strong>El:</strong> The (masculine singular) - e.g., <em>el perro</em> (the dog)</li><li><strong>La:</strong> The (feminine singular) - e.g., <em>la casa</em> (the house)</li><li><strong>Los:</strong> The (masculine plural) - e.g., <em>los perros</em> (the dogs)</li><li><strong>Las:</strong> The (feminine plural) - e.g., <em>las casas</em> (the houses)</li></ul><h3>Common Nouns:</h3><ul><li><strong>Hombre:</strong> man</li><li><strong>Mujer:</strong> woman</li><li><strong>Niño/Niña:</strong> boy/girl</li><li><strong>Agua:</strong> water</li><li><strong>Comida:</strong> food</li></ul><p>Practice identifying gender by looking at the noun's ending (often -o for masculine, -a for feminine).</p>"
