    "level": "Beginner",
    "content": "<p>Spanish has two verbs for \"to be\": <strong>ser</strong> and <strong>estar</strong>. Their usage depends on whether the state is permanent or temporary.</p><h3>Ser (Permanent/Essential Qualities):</h3><ul><li><strong>Origin:</strong> <em>Soy de España.</em> (I am from Spain.)</li><li><strong>Identity:</strong> <em>Ella es doctora.</em> (She is a doctor.)</li><li><strong>Time/Date:</strong> <em>Son las tres.</em> (It is three o'clock.)</li><li><strong>Characteristics:</strong> <em>Él es alto.</em> (He is tall.)</li></ul><h3>Estar (Temporary States/Location):</h3><ul><li><strong>Location:</strong> <em>Estoy en casa.</em> (I am at home.)</li><li><strong>Feelings/Emotions:</strong> <em>Estoy feliz.</em> (I am happy.)</li><li><strong>Temporary Conditions:</strong> <em>La puerta está abierta.</em> (The door is open.)</li><li><strong>Health:</strong> <em>Estoy enfermo.</em> (I am sick.)</li></ul><p>This is a challenging but vital concept. Practice with many examples!</p>"
